values: I haven't posted in ages and figured, "You know...I haven't posted in ages!" So here I am, posting. Talk with you all...well next time :p

Though I'm a bit late in reporting it, its been a busy couple weeks. I'll start off with I'm a Father now. My Girlfriend gave birth to little Dustin Alexander Lower on May 2, 2005 at 12:19 am Which happen to of been his due date. Its reported only 3% of babies born are ever born on their due dates.  Gotta love beating the odds. Mmmmm Life is good HeHe. Anyways, shall talk with you soon.

Matt

I'm getting in the mood for Christmas a bit early this year.  Not sure why but already have a tree up and decorated, going to put lights up around the apartment soon as well. Done most of my Christmas shopping too. It's starting to get pretty cold, already had our first snow of the season though it barely if at all touched the ground.  Well anyways, I have a few things to get done, shall talk with you all soon :)

Spring seams to have come a little early this year.  Buds are already sprouting on trees and flowers alike.  Its getting warm enough that I wont be able to wear my favorite leather coat, oh the horror HeHeHe.  Alas the sun is starting to shine and I'll have to hide under my sunglasses.  Its times like these that I feel very much like a vampire.  Oh well, that's my life for you.

Now if I can just get off my ass of late and get the laundry done.  On top of that I've been having a major entertainment problem as of late.  Absolutely nothing has been satisfying my need for more than a few short minutes. My guess is that I need something completely new to do.  As far as I know it doesn't need to be totally radically dangerous or foreign, just different.

Course it doesn't help that until then, my sleeping habits have been changing constantly, I keep watching countless DVDs to pass the boredom, have been eating food that just isn't good for me to the point I'm craving salads now (not that that's a bad thing to crave).  Anyways, hopefully I'll find something soon so I can get back to normal.

Talk with you later,
Wraith the Pirate King

Well its been crazy just after Xmas time here in Bellingham.  We didn't have a white Xmas but the snow sure came in after.  It started off fairly nice, a little snow that didn't really stick at all.  A few days later the snow just started coming and coming.  I had to take Ashley home and managed not to be able to get around a turn near her house so had to walk the rest of the way.  I spent the night there cause had no chance of getting back home in those conditions.  The next day I managed to get home fairly easily.  Ashley came over again and wasn't too hard to get her home but the next day I couldn't get even close to taking her home.  Her step-dad had to get his 4x4 Suburban and pick us both up cause we were definitely stuck.  So I spent the night over there again.  The next day we went and dug my car out of the snow and went home.  Later on that night Ashley's step-dad came and picked her up cause there was no chance I could do it. These past couple days I've been able to do the driving but only cause there's no new snow to speak of but supposedly tonight and tomorrow there is supposed to be a lot more snow to endure. The snow sure is picture worthy but I just can't stand ice and the cold!!!  Too much Californian blood in my system still but I am adjusting more and more.  I was walking in the snow to Ashley's house (see above) and the cold wasn't bugging me which is very unusual.
Well guess I've babbled on about the weather too much as it is.  Talk with you all later :)
Wraith

Well really yesterday, the 20th, was my birthday but oh well.  It was a pretty good day, went out to dinner at Red Robin, got sang to while wearing those funky glasses and holding a couple balloons and the vanilla sunday with a candle.  The rest of night was spent game playing.  Well anyways, not much else to it so talk with you all later :)

I've been busy playing Star Wars Galaxies to which I run a pirate guild called "The Pendulum", if you care to visit the website for the guild its www.geocities.com/nightwraithx Anyways, aside of that, not too much has been going on.  I have started writing more often though still not enough to get much accomplished.  Hopefully someday I'll finish one of my novels and hopefully I'll do that before I start any more, Already have 2 in the works and a few poems that are far from completion.  I just am too easily distracted.  Well if anyone has any ideas how to help me focus on whatever I may need ot focus on, please send me your advice, it would be welcomed, and thanked for especially if it works! HeHeHe.

Well, until next time,
Matt

Well I got to see X-Men 2 the other day which I enjoyed and think it was better than the first.  Course without the first the second one would of sucked royally HeHe.

I can't wait for Matrix: Reloaded to come out in a few days.  It looks so good!!!  Course I'm a Matrix fan to start with so perhaps I'm a bit biased.

Can't wait for upcoming films that aren't so close to release either and here they are:  Spiderman 2, Lord of the Rings - The Return of the King, Star Wars - Episode III, Time Line, Dare Devil 2, X-Men 3, Harry Potter 3, The Matirx 3, and there is likely some others that while big on my mind just aren't coming to mind HeHeHe anyways say it with me...

MOVIES!!! MOVIES!!! MOVIES!!!

Mostly due to one simple reason. I FORGOT!!! Yes, I have literally forgotten about Live journal.  Don't know what made me remember this time but I have and so I'm posting before I forget once again.  Nothing new has really happened.  But I will say this.  For all you RPG lovers out there, you just HAVE to go play "Suikoden III" for the PS2.  It has to be one of the greatest RPG ever to date.  Endless hours of play time, tons of chars to play as, mini games, things to find, diverse battles/tactics and monsters, Great story line, side quests, Mass scale type battles, intrigue and mystery galore.  You name it, its there and the graphics are very good to boot. Perhaps that's the reason for forgetting about Live Journal.  Well Anyways, back to gaming for me.

MISSION:  You are to go seek Suikoden III and evaluate it for yourself.  If you find it interesting, BUY IT!!!  Its far too long of a game to rent, so might as well pay the, I think it was $20 to purchase. Enjoy, I know I have.

X-Mas and New Years were pretty good for me, hope you all had one as well =)

MISSION:  You are all to Make (if you hadn't already) your new year's resolutions.  And are actually going to stick to them this year =) Good luck!

Today was just an overall really good day (in which I wont go into any details) But was very good =)

MISSION:
You are to go out either as soon as you read this or the very next day and enjoy the entire day, go out and do stuff, and have as much fun as possible.  This message will self destruct in 10 seconds.

I'm not sure what I'm feeling.  Its kinda like being restless, NEEDing to do a lot of things, but having nothing to do, so I try and stay up as long as I can to do stuff and I do all that I can think of and nothing satisfies it.  Course then I get tired and go to bed and try to get comfy but I can't sleep for several hours cause I'm wondering what I had forgotten to do or try.  So the next day I start all over and try as many different things as I can and once again nothing works.  My guess is I just need something not just new but RADICALLY new to satisfy this need of mine but what this completely new thing is, I sure don't know what it is.

THE  MISSION:

Whoever reads this, if you have any ideas for stuff that either perhaps is common for you but different for others or just something you think I'd like, please tell me what it is.  I really need a change or addition to my life or I shall go insane for sure (well further insane than currently) If you find something that I just love to do, I'll be your new best friend *all smiles*

Yours in Darkness,
Night Wraith X

At least better than they were a week ago or so but still have a LONG ways to go before I'm back to where I was my best.  Not sure if that's even possible anymore but suppose we shall see in the long run.  But for now I'm surviving and living the best I can.

Have had the urge to write so much lately yet each time I stare at the paper blankly.  Its driving me nuts not to write my stories and poetry. I NEED to write again, this writers block of mine must go now!!!

I'm also having a entertainment slump.  I need new forms of entertainment or at least new forms of old entertainment.  Something to get the blood flowing, heart pounding, or at the very least intrigue me to no end.

Well suppose that's all for now, I'm hungry... would you like to satisfy my need?

how would you commit suicide?

I turned 25 back on the 20th.  Been having fun spending time with Ashley and while my sleeping habits have totally gone to shit, I was enjoying life.  Perhaps I will again later....but not right now...

I haven't been making any journal entries for a reason.....there has been absolutely nothing worth saying.  Its been so utterly boring and probably will continue to be as such. Course have had the chance to watch a lot of movies. Course everyone has been far to busy to do anything and me not busy enough....so I'm basically home alone with nothing to do and no one to go out with to have any fun.  Oh wells....hopefully it'll pass. *REALLY hates being bored*

Okay, perhaps I have been relaxing too much this Vacation.  I'm bored and need something new to do.  I just can't seem to find anything new that looks fun.  Of course I'll keep looking but would be nice to have already found it, whatever it is.

Saw the double feature for Spiderman and MIB2....Although have seen the movies before. I went with Ashley so pretty much spend the whole day with her.  Ahh I Love her so much.  She was definitely in a trouble maker mood.  Would definitely have to of been there cause no time worth explaining would do any good.  Anyways....that's my post for the day.

Been a few days since my last post so thought I should =)  Hasn't been too much going on although finally got my Cellphones' Voicemail to work HeHeHe *yawns* course this is past 3am so am quite tired....but can't sleep.  Just a bit of insomnia but oh well. Gotta Love my Ashley too...We are always together and having a good time..Mmm Love her soooo much =)

Anyways talk with you all later =)

Well I'm back home..so a lot of things have happened and well....As much as I like writing in my journal about all that's happened... Think it would be easier to just have you ask me what's happened or the like cause 3 weeks worth plus a few other days is a lot of info to cover.  I'm quite tired though....been a long vacation (for me since I hate traveling)

Well 1st off went and saw Ashley for a few hours after waking up *Big Grin* , then did some packing for my trip to New York...deposited some money then ate dinner...then went to see Ashley again *oooooooh* And am currently packing some more while listening to music waiting for Ashley to call.....which should be soon I hope.

Spent today (the 28th) with Ashley again....went to the mall....got some CDs came home.....had a good time and messed around on the computer.... Life is just soooo goood =) Although I can't imagine it getting better....I know it can and will.  It just boggles my mind to think of it all.....just sooo much to do and just a life time to do it in.....We'll find a way though.

Today I graduated from college (Bellingham Technical College for those who may not know) So just got home and can relax knowing I'M DONE!!!! At least until I have to find a job but for now.....Can relax =) WooHoo

P.S. Ashley is sooooo cute HeHeHe.......Just gotta Love her....can't wait to be with her again...its only been a few days but Ugh....Need to be with her so badly and plus......she's been needing me too..I'm certainly addicted to her as she is too me =)

Spend a few hours with Ashley which are ALWAYS great....Just Gotta Love her soooo much.

Then spent part of the day helping my dad move a couch onto his truck bed to give to a friend that lives on Orcas Island......and am now home talking with Ashley again...As I try to do the entire day, everyday, 24 hours a day if possible HeHeHe

Just Love her sooooo much =)

Good and bad days keep coming and going......can't wait till schools done....only a few more days but UGH....hate feeling like this and nothing to calm me down.....Ashley's been too busy and well haven't been in a music mood lately so......Ugh....Ugh....and oh UGH

Friday (the 14th) Was AWESOME!!!! Had the greatest time with Ashley.  Sure we both had colds and stuff but they didn't seem to have any impact....in fact think we made each other feel soooo good that the colds were beaten back =) Mmmmmmmm I just Love her soooo much.  Can't wait till next time.  If only the time we had was longer but oooh we used the time very well =) Mmmmmm I miss her soo much....Even if I'm talking with her online or on phone....just doesn't quite have the same feeling as when we are together.  Well until next time though right?  And I hope for a lifetime full of those next times =)

My Internship ended today so my schedule just got a whole lot easier! Can see Ashley more and also get more assorted school work done now that I have class labs once again.

Life can be cool....well aside of it sorta being hot temperature wise....how annoying. What's more annoying is that had I been still in California....this would be a nice, somewhat cool day.... Maybe I really have adjusted to WA weather....a bit. Still can take it better than most Washingtonians.

My nose is really bugging me though...and is getting sore from blowing it all the time.  Through hurts a bit too but not as bad as yesterday or day before.

Ashley seems to be feeling a little better but not much.....Wish there was something I could do to help out more... Hopefully today will be better for her than the past few days too.

Just gotta Love the Ashley!!! =)

Sick once again......its getting quite annoying.  I want my health back but not sure where it has gone to.  Am feeling better today than yesterday though.

Course Ashley is sick as well.....seems we tend to do these things at about the same time.....don't know why but just happens.  Would be really cool if it was good stuff but being sick is certainly not cool.

Well anyways.....we'll both be better soon I'm sure

You're excited about life and in touch with yourself and nature. Tell me, do I have this straight? Virtues: You appreciate humor like none other. Puns might even spark laughter in you (TEHY R FUNNI). You seek adventure and connection with your surroundings. You seek friends who will not only share laughs with you but actually form a deep bond of trust and empathy beneath the surface. You look for adventure and courage in people, and variation is necessary to keep you under control. You see yourself as multi-faceted, so you need people who can see you in your many lights. You're constantly trying to figure yourself out while analyzing the people around you. Silly, silly people. Aspirations: You can't decide what you want to be yet, but you know you want it to be adventures and interesting, with constant changes. You don't know what love will do for you yet, but it's competing with adventure for a place in your heart. An internal conflict has begun: can you be a successful worker, lover, and parent all at once? Quirks: Noise of any sort is irritating when you're in the mood. Smacking gum, loud chewing, humming- it's about as pleasing as bodily noises. You dislike emaciated people because of jealousy and just plain disgust. You're a procrastinator but a hard worker, too. Factors: You need constant attention and support. You're high-maintenance, but a great, reliable friend. Finished a Project for Computer User Support II today.  Went better than I expected, but then they usually do.

Meanwhile I started my Internship on Monday of last week (I forget the numeric date but...) Has been hard work since I have only a lunch break for 7 hours, course today its going to be a full 9 hours with the same lunch break so am going to be tired.  I know there are those that work 12 hour or more days but 8 is the longest I have as yet and if you haven't done it or gotten used to it...its quite tiring.  Wouldn't be so tiring if I wasn't getting sick though... Either that or I'm actually getting stressed.  Can't remember ever being stressed before in my life... so maybe it is stress and not getting sick.  Either way I'm quite busy, and am looking for relief.

Sure it had a rocky start, but was good in the end =)

On another subject..Wheres my prey? *prowls*

Well Yesterday did get a lot better (although a majorly important part did not occur....)  Still things were definitely good when I saw Star Wars Ep. II.  I had thought it was just going to be a bit better than Ep I but had no idea it'd be WAY better HeHeHe.  Sure it had some corny dialog now and then but sometimes corny dialog is the best.  Still WoW WoW WoW  1st Spiderman now Star Wars II....Spring has been a goooood movie season =)  (And wasn't just my opinion...the entire crowd in the pact theater was whistling and laughing and hollering at the movie in a very good way)

Well yesterday (Wednesday) Was a damn good day...wonder if today will be just as good or not.
Also Star Wars: Attack of the Clones is out in theaters today.  And if you know me....you know I'm a big Star Wars fan so will probably try to make it but I have doubts cause of the masses of people probably trying to get there first oh well...I'll make it sooner or later =)
Anyways..today seems to be going good so far...can it get better? Yes I do believe it can and will =) =) =)
